-- BP Russian partners say corporate row solved
-- 
-- Thu Sep 4, 2008 4:37am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/04/us-tnkbp-deal-idUSWLA901620080904

 

 MOSCOW  (Reuters) - BP's ( BP.L ) Russia-connected co-owners in oil company TNK-BP TNBPI.RTS said on Thursday they had signed a memorandum with the oil major to solve a protracted corporate conflict. 

 "We just signed the memorandum, we will release full details later today... It basically means the corporate conflict is solved," Stan Polovets, chief executive of Russian consortium Alfa-Access-Renova told Reuters. (Reporting by Dmitry Zhdannikov; editing by  Melissa Akin )